&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Denver Broncos are one of the most popular franchises in all of sports. Whether judged by the measure of wins and championships, attendance, national television exposure or by the Broncos&#39; reputation locally and throughout the NFL, there are few parallels in the world of professional sports. We are dedicated to being the best team to cheer for, play for, and work for across all of sports. We are looking for employees who are passionate about what they do, have fun doing it, and proud to represent the Denver Broncos Football Club and Empower Field at Mile High.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Kitchen Lead Steward / Porter plays a critical role in maintaining a clean, efficient, and high-performing culinary operation. This position ensures that all kitchen, nutrition, and service areas are organized, sanitized, and fully equipped to support chefs, dietitians, players, and staff. The Lead Steward oversees daily stewardship duties, checking in purveyors, coordinates porters, maintains inventory of cleaning supplies and equipment, and ensures the kitchen runs at a high standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Daily Operations &amp;amp; Sanitation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead all dishwashing, cleaning, and sanitation operations throughout kitchens, prep areas, and service spaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain strict cleanliness standards in compliance with local health codes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Checking in and putting away all purveyors. Assist with inventory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stocking beverages and snacks throughout the facility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all equipment (grills, ranges, steam jackets, dish machines, sinks, floor scrubbers) are functioning properly and cleaned regularly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee trash, recycling, composting, and proper waste procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Leadership&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise steward/porter staff, schedule shifts, delegate tasks, and train new employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide direction during peak meal periods, game days, and special events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a positive and efficient back-of-house environment aligned with team culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Equipment &amp;amp; Inventory&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and maintain par levels of cleaning supplies, chemicals, and sanitation tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with receiving, organizing, and storing deliveries, ensuring proper rotation (FIFO)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Control Inventory of beverages, snacks, coffee, disposables and chemicals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep storage rooms, walk-ins, and dry goods areas organized, clean and safe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support for Kitchen &amp;amp; Nutrition Staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure chefs have clean tools, equipment, and workstations ready for service and meal prep&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with basic prep tasks as needed (e.g., transporting equipment, organizing small wares)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support coffee service operations for players, coaches, and team person&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate quick turnover of equipment and dishes between meals, meetings, and special events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Minimum Requirements:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years of experience as a steward, porter, or similar back-of-house role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of commercial kitchen sanitation standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift 50+ lbs and stand/walk for extended periods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable, punctual, and able to work flexible schedules (early mornings, late nights, weekends)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lead, train, and motivate a small team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
